Package javelin.controller.kit

Class Kit

  • java.lang.Object
    • javelin.controller.kit.Kit
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    Assassin, Barbarian, Bard, Cleric, Druid, Fighter, Monk, Paladin, Ranger, Rogue, Wizard
    public abstract class Kit
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable
    Kits represent sets of Upgrades that constitute a role a character may have a play in. As much inspired on AD&D kits as actual character classes, these are used on the AdventurersGuild and Academy types as means of upgrading Combatants. Kits are usually created by piecing together 3 to 7 lowest-level upgrades.

    alex
